00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,539
and it really releases
the serotonin, and...

486
00:42:23,624 --> 00:42:26,584
Hey, man, this time we'll do it my way.

487
00:42:33,467 --> 00:42:35,385
Well, hello, puppy.

488
00:42:35,469 --> 00:42:39,055
Did you come for some of Grandma's
butter bean dumplings?

489
00:42:39,973 --> 00:42:41,224
You wait right there.

490
00:42:41,308 --> 00:42:43,893
One of these days,
I'm gonna pound y'all to the ground.

491
00:42:43,977 --> 00:42:45,978
No more Mr. Nice Guy.

492
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:52,902
Look at you.
You are quite the little actor, huh?

493
00:42:52,986 --> 00:42:55,405
I haven't eaten like this in ages.

494
00:42:55,489 --> 00:42:58,574
Hey, look, my stomach's distended!
How great is that?

495
00:42:58,659 --> 00:43:01,577
Yeah, well, don't get used to it.
We gotta keep moving.

496
00:43:01,662 --> 00:43:04,580
But this place is a gold mine.
What's wrong with you?

497
00:43:04,665 --> 00:43:09,252
Every week new RVs bring us
new suckers who bring us new food.

498
00:43:09,336 --> 00:43:12,088
Look around! It's perfect.

499
00:43:17,010 --> 00:43:19,095
Do my eyes deceive me?

500
00:43:19,179 --> 00:43:22,140
Is this some apparition
I see before me?

501
00:43:22,933 --> 00:43:26,436
Or could it be my hero?

502
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:29,105
Oh, my gosh,
oh, my gosh, oh, my gosh!

503
00:43:31,191 --> 00:43:35,445
You're Bolt, the Superdog!
You're fully awesome!

504
00:43:36,613 --> 00:43:42,285
- Wait a minute. You know this dog?
- I do. He is fully awesome.

505
00:43:42,369 --> 00:43:45,037
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
We've established that. Who are you?

506
00:43:45,122 --> 00:43:48,374
- I'm Rhino.
- Rhino the hamster.

507
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:50,960
Well, you know,
my ancestry isn't all hamster.

508
00:43:51,044 --> 00:43:54,964
I'm one-sixteenth wolfwith, you know,
a little wolverine in there somewhere,

509
00:43:55,048 --> 00:43:56,799
but that's besides the point.

510
00:43:56,884 --> 00:44:01,721
We have before us a legend,
Bolt, the Superdog.

511
00:44:02,181 --> 00:44:04,056
He can outrun speeding missiles

512
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:07,477
and burn through solid metal
with his heat vision.

513
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:12,899
And best of all, he can obliterate
large structures with his superbark!

514
00:44:12,983 --> 00:44:15,902
Wait a minute.
You've seen the superbark?

515
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:18,070
Have you been observing me?

516
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:22,492
- Oh, yeah! I watch you all the time.
- That's incredible.

517
00:44:22,576 --> 00:44:23,993
Oh, it's nothing, really.

518
00:44:24,077 --> 00:44:25,995
But I'm always so vigilant.

519
00:44:26,079 --> 00:44:29,916
No one can evade my detection.
You're a phantom.

520
00:44:31,585 --> 00:44:34,253
If you say so. Hey, check it out.

521
00:44:35,756 --> 00:44:41,761
Take a gander at this Bolt action.
Scary, huh? It's like we're twins.

522
00:44:41,887 --> 00:44:44,764
Yeah. Scary.

523
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:47,517
So, where's Penny?

524
00:44:47,601 --> 00:44:49,769
She was kidnapped
by the Green-Eyed Man.

525
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:54,273
Kidnapped? This is terrible!
She could be in grave...

526
00:44:54,358 --> 00:44:57,610
Grave danger. I know.
But I've captured this cat.

527
00:44:57,694 --> 00:45:01,280
An agent of the Green-Eyed Man,
I presume?

528
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:04,450
You presume correctly.
She's taking me to Penny.

529
00:45:04,535 --> 00:45:10,122
You, you are vile vermin.
How do you sleep at night?

530
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:14,961
Penny's the most wonderful person
ever, and she loves Bolt.

531
00:45:15,045 --> 00:45:18,798
And he's awesome,
and you're a monster!

532
00:45:18,882 --> 00:45:23,052
How dare you disrupt their relationship
with your evil!

533
00:45:23,136 --> 00:45:25,471
Die! Die!

534
00:45:25,597 --> 00:45:28,057
I can take her, Bolty.
Let me at them. Die!

535
00:45:28,141 --> 00:45:31,602
- Die!
- Easy, easy, Rhino. Easy.

536
00:45:31,979 --> 00:45:34,814
You're right. We need her alive.

537
00:45:36,233 --> 00:45:37,900
- "We"?
- Yes!

538
00:45:37,985 --> 00:45:41,487
Bolt, I can be a valuable addition
to your team.

539
00:45:41,613 --> 00:45:43,573
- I'm listening.
- I'm lightning-quick.

540
00:45:43,657 --> 00:45:48,327
I have razor-sharp reflexes,
and I'm a master of stealth.

541
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:52,164
Plus, I'll keep the cat in check.

542
00:45:53,458 --> 00:45:54,834
The road'll be rough.

543
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:56,085
I have a ball.

544
00:45:56,169 --> 00:45:57,503
There's no turning back.

545
00:45:57,588 --> 00:45:59,589
Guess I'll have to roll with the punches.

546
00:45:59,673 --> 00:46:01,507
Easy won't be part of the equation.

547
00:46:01,592 --> 00:46:02,592
Promise?

548
00:46:02,676 --> 00:46:05,261
I gotta warn you.
Going into the belly of the beast,

549
00:46:05,345 --> 00:46:06,679
danger at every turn.

550
00:46:06,763 --> 00:46:09,015
I eat danger for breakfast.

551
00:46:09,099 --> 00:46:10,433
You hungry?

552
00:46:11,518 --> 00:46:12,852
Starving!

553
00:46:12,936 --> 00:46:14,437
Welcome aboard!

554
00:46:15,689 --> 00:46:19,108
Hey. Can we talk for a second?

555
00:46:19,484 --> 00:46:21,027
I don't know what's going on here,

556
00:46:21,153 --> 00:46:25,781
but I'm just a little bit concerned about
the number of lunatics on this trip.

557
00:46:25,866 --> 00:46:27,533
My limit is one.

558
00:46:27,659 --> 00:46:28,701
He's coming with us.

559
00:46:28,827 --> 00:46:31,370
But I... Hey!

560
00:46:31,455 --> 00:46:33,623
Move it, prisoner.
We're losing daylight.

561
00:46:33,707 --> 00:46:37,668
I agree. Now,
we need to find a fast set ofwheels.

562
00:46:38,545 --> 00:46:41,505
I've got a better idea. Follow me.

563
00:46:53,894 --> 00:46:57,396
Okay. So what we do here is
we give the target a quick flyover,

564
00:46:57,481 --> 00:47:00,232
we adjust the trajectory
and then land dead center.

565
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:01,984
Am I missing anything, Rhino?

566
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:04,487
Just the knowledge that every minute
spent in your company

567
00:47:04,571 --> 00:47:06,906
becomes the new greatest minute
of my life.

568
00:47:06,990 --> 00:47:12,078
No! Forget it! How do you say
"No way I'm doing this" in crazy?

569
00:47:12,162 --> 00:47:13,829
Calm down, cat. You're with me.

570
00:47:13,914 --> 00:47:15,665
That's the problem!

571
00:47:17,084 --> 00:47:18,417
Would you relax?

572
00:47:18,543 --> 00:47:22,380
Every time he did this on the magic box
it was awesome.

573
00:47:25,717 --> 00:47:26,759
Magic what?

574
00:47:26,843 --> 00:47:29,595
You know,
the magic box people stare at.

575
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:32,598
Wait a minute. Does this magic box
have moving pictures on it?

576
00:47:32,724 --> 00:47:35,184
Yeah, and Bolt's pictures are the best.

577
00:47:35,268 --> 00:47:39,355
Bolt's pictures. Of course!
He's from a... Oh, no!

578
00:47:39,439 --> 00:47:41,691
Oh, no. No, wait, wait.
Bolt, dog, hear me out.

579
00:47:41,775 --> 00:47:44,527
Let it begin. Let it begin. Let it begin!

580
00:47:44,611 --> 00:47:47,780
Wait! You are not a superhero...

581
00:47:55,372 --> 00:47:57,206
What are you doing?

582
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:14,557
Mittens!

583
00:48:14,641 --> 00:48:17,059
Mittens, take my paw! I need you alive!

584
00:48:17,144 --> 00:48:19,812
You're crazy! Stay away from me!

585
00:48:19,938 --> 00:48:22,064
Take my paw. I'll save you.

586
00:48:22,149 --> 00:48:24,817
No, you won't! You're not really a...

587
00:48:42,002 --> 00:48:43,127
Bolt!

588
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:47,089
Saboteur.

589
00:48:49,843 --> 00:48:52,178
You moron, stop it.
I'm trying to help him.

590
00:48:52,262 --> 00:48:54,638
Help him? Yeah, right.

591
00:48:56,016 --> 00:48:58,684
Don't worry, Bolt. I'll stop her!

592
00:49:08,862 --> 00:49:10,613
I can't hold it.

593
00:49:14,993 --> 00:49:16,619
Let go, you monster!

594
00:49:16,703 --> 00:49:17,953
Bolt!

595
00:49:48,151 --> 00:49:50,653
The real world hurts, doesn't it?

596
00:49:50,737 --> 00:49:53,322
But you wouldn't know about that,
would you?

597
00:49:53,406 --> 00:49:56,116
Get down here, cat.
We don't have time for this.

598
00:49:56,201 --> 00:49:57,827
I'll get a ladder.

599
00:49:58,829 --> 00:50:03,707
Look, genius, you're part of a TV show.
You know what that is? Television?

600
00:50:03,792 --> 00:50:09,755
It's entertainment for people. It's fake.
Nothing you think is real is real!

601
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:11,173
That's preposterous.

602
00:50:11,258 --> 00:50:12,341
Think about it, Bolt.

603
00:50:12,425 --> 00:50:15,010
Since you got lost, none of your powers
are working, are they?

604
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:18,013
For the first time, you're hungry,
you're bleeding.

605
00:50:18,098 --> 00:50:21,100
I mean, do you really think that
you were born with a birthmark

606
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:24,937
in the exact shape of a lightning bolt?

607
00:50:25,021 --> 00:50:27,356
It's my mark of power, cat.

608
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:29,567
It's the mark of a makeup artist, dog.

609
00:50:29,651 --> 00:50:32,236
You're ridiculous. Now get down here.

610
00:50:34,072 --> 00:50:35,155
No.

611
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:39,034
Mittens, so help me,
I will superbark you out of that tree.

612
00:50:39,119 --> 00:50:42,371
Yeah. Go nuts.
Let's see how that works out for you.

613
00:50:42,455 --> 00:50:44,540
You leave me no choice.

614
00:50:53,300 --> 00:50:58,721
The superbark. Scary, scary.
Yeah, that's really, really super.

615
00:51:01,141 --> 00:51:03,559
It's not true. It's just not true.

616
00:51:07,564 --> 00:51:10,482
Wow. That one felt really super.

617
00:51:10,942 --> 00:51:12,735
Wait. No, it didn't.

618
00:51:14,487 --> 00:51:18,574
Okay, okay. I get the idea.
You could stop now.

619
00:51:18,658 --> 00:51:24,872
That's enough. Seriously, dog, stop.
I'm not kidding. Would you stop? It's...

620
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:30,920
Okay, fine! You're a superdog.

621
00:51:31,004 --> 00:51:34,840
Bolt, be quiet, please!
Bolt, we gotta run!

622
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:36,842
Bolt!

623
00:51:36,927 --> 00:51:38,260
Come here!

624
00:52:08,291 --> 00:52:14,421
Look who we found, young lady.
It's Bolt! They found him.

625
00:52:14,506 --> 00:52:15,547
Bolt!

626
00:52:15,632 --> 00:52:18,509
Yeah, that's right.
The little puppy dog.

627
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:25,432
That is not Bolt.

628
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:29,853
Well, that depends on
how you look at it.

629
00:52:30,313 --> 00:52:34,441
You know, when I was little,
I wanted a bicycle for my birthday,

630
00:52:34,526 --> 00:52:37,194
but my parents got me
a baseball glove.

631
00:52:37,278 --> 00:52:39,363
So, you know what I did?

632
00:52:39,447 --> 00:52:43,993
I pretended that baseball glove
was a bicycle,

633
00:52:44,577 --> 00:52:47,037
and I rode it to school every day.

634
00:52:47,372 --> 00:52:48,747
True story.

635
00:52:49,374 --> 00:52:51,166
It's not him.

636
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:53,127
I think it's him. I do.

637
00:52:54,671 --> 00:52:58,882
Thank you. Look, kid.
It's time we were honest with you.

638
00:52:58,967 --> 00:53:02,052
Lfwe don't get back into production,
people are going to lose theirjobs.

639
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:03,846
Good people, with families.

640
00:53:03,930 --> 00:53:05,347
But Bolt's still out there, and...

641
00:53:05,432 --> 00:53:07,099
Now, we feel for you,

642
00:53:07,183 --> 00:53:09,351
and the last thing we wanna do
is ask a little girl

643
00:53:09,436 --> 00:53:12,813
to make a grown-up decision,
but it's come to that.

644
00:53:12,897 --> 00:53:14,857
We need you to move on.

645
00:53:15,859 --> 00:53:18,444
We need you to let Bolt go.

646
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:48,223
Must be made of Styrofoam.

647
00:53:49,350 --> 00:53:52,478
No, no! No, no, no, please, please,
it can't end like this!

648
00:53:52,562 --> 00:53:55,606
Stop worrying, cat!
I'll get us out of here.

649
00:53:55,690 --> 00:53:59,985
You can't, Bolt! You got nothing!
No super strength, no superbark...

650
00:54:01,738 --> 00:54:03,447
And no heat vision.

651
00:54:03,907 --> 00:54:05,074
Listen to me, okay?

652
00:54:05,158 --> 00:54:09,119
We are being taken to a place where
humans go animal shopping, all right?

653
00:54:09,204 --> 00:54:12,414
And this is what humans do.
They always pick the cute ones.

654
00:54:12,499 --> 00:54:17,127
The ones that look like you, Bolt.
But the rest of us never come back out.

655
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:20,047
I said I'll get us out of here, all right?

656
00:54:29,766 --> 00:54:31,016
My hero.

657
00:54:46,199 --> 00:54:50,035
Ring, ring. Who is it? Destiny?

658
00:54:51,371 --> 00:54:53,956
I've been expecting your call.

659
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:31,660
Would you give it up already?

660
00:55:31,744 --> 00:55:34,872
You're liquefying
whatever brains you have left.

661
00:55:35,415 --> 00:55:41,503
I cannot be contained in any container.
You quitter. Watch this.

662
00:55:50,013 --> 00:55:52,097
I did it! I'm back!

663
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:55,434
That Styrofoam is wicked stuff.

664
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:57,603
Fully awesome!

665
00:55:57,687 --> 00:56:01,607
There's no truck that I know
that can keep in Bolt and Rhino!

666
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:04,776
Rhino? What are you doing here?

667
00:56:05,111 --> 00:56:07,529
Nothing.
I was enjoying an evening stroll

668
00:56:07,614 --> 00:56:11,700
and thought I'd just pop the hatch
on that containment unit.

669
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:15,120
You opened the door?

670
00:56:15,246 --> 00:56:16,955
Yes, I did!

671
00:56:18,291 --> 00:56:23,378
That's great, Rhino.
Yeah, that's really good.

672
00:56:23,463 --> 00:56:26,632
All right. Let's go get the prisoner back.

673
00:56:42,815 --> 00:56:44,316
I can't do it.

674
00:56:47,320 --> 00:56:48,987
What did you say?

675
00:56:49,572 --> 00:56:50,781
I can't.

676
00:56:51,658 --> 00:56:52,991
Who are you?

677
00:56:53,117 --> 00:56:55,244
Rhino, you just don't under...

678
00:56:55,328 --> 00:56:57,829
- You are Bolt.
- But I'm not a...

679
00:56:57,914 --> 00:57:00,916
Who singlehandedly destroyed
the Green-Eyed Mars undersea labs?

680
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:02,084
Me, but...

681
00:57:02,168 --> 00:57:07,339
And who foiled his plan to infiltrate
the Olympics with gymnastic cyborgs?

682
00:57:07,423 --> 00:57:10,008
- Who, Bolt, who? Who?
- Me, but none of it was...

683
00:57:10,093 --> 00:57:13,095
You! You can, Bolt,

684
00:57:13,179 --> 00:57:15,180
because all over this planet,

685
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:18,267
there are animals
who feel like they can't.

686
00:57:18,935 --> 00:57:24,940
Like a little hamster who once spent
his days in an RV park,

687
00:57:25,441 --> 00:57:29,528
dreaming of the day when he, too,
would save a little girl from danger

688
00:57:29,654 --> 00:57:35,784
and be told, "You did it.
You did it, Rhino. You saved the day."

689
00:57:36,452 --> 00:57:38,620
They need a hero, Bolt.

690
00:57:38,705 --> 00:57:42,874
Someone who, no matter
what the odds, will do what's right.

691
00:57:43,001 --> 00:57:47,296
They need a hero to tell them
that sometimes the impossible

692
00:57:47,380 --> 00:57:51,842
can become possible
if you're awesome!

693
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:56,805
Well,
you're right about one thing, Rhino.

694
00:57:57,640 --> 00:57:59,683
Mittens does need a hero,

695
00:58:01,853 --> 00:58:03,228
and I guess I'll have to do.

696
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:08,233
Such modesty!
Now, who's going to save that cat?

697
00:58:08,318 --> 00:58:10,319
- Me.
- Who? Tell me who!

698
00:58:10,403 --> 00:58:11,486
Me.

699
00:58:13,990 --> 00:58:15,657
I'll get my ball.

700
00:58:31,341 --> 00:58:32,716
Over there.

701
00:58:35,511 --> 00:58:36,928
There it is.

702
00:58:42,226 --> 00:58:46,938
This'll be just like the time you
infiltrated Calico's Arctic hover-base!

703
00:58:47,774 --> 00:58:50,275
But it's not gonna be
exactly like that, Rhino.

704
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:53,612
We're gonna have to do things
a little differently.

705
00:58:55,406 --> 00:58:57,366
Stealth mode.

706
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:03,205
Good night, Ester.

707
00:59:03,289 --> 00:59:04,915
Good night, Lloyd.

708
00:59:11,547 --> 00:59:12,714
Lloyd?

709
00:59:15,718 --> 00:59:18,053
Lloyd Spoon,
you jump out and scare me,

710
00:59:18,137 --> 00:59:20,806
and I'm gonna pepper-spray you again!

711
00:59:24,727 --> 00:59:27,813
I swear, it's like I work with toddlers.

712
00:59:31,776 --> 00:59:34,069
Threat nullified.

713
00:59:38,324 --> 00:59:40,242
I feel alive.

714
00:59:45,498 --> 00:59:47,165
There's a guard.

715
00:59:47,291 --> 00:59:48,834
I'll snap his neck.

716
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:51,586
We need to get him away
from that door.

717
00:59:58,928 --> 01:00:01,430
- Ball?
- Ball?

718
01:00:01,514 --> 01:00:05,350
- Ball? Ball? Ball?
- Ball! Ball! Ball!

719
01:00:06,978 --> 01:00:11,273
I'm just... I'm read... I'm just...
Just pipe down!

720
01:00:23,828 --> 01:00:25,036
Mittens?

721
01:00:26,289 --> 01:00:30,459
Bolt? What are you doing here?

722
01:00:30,793 --> 01:00:32,377
I'm busting you out.

723
01:00:32,462 --> 01:00:36,882
You... You came all the way back here
for me?

724
01:00:37,008 --> 01:00:38,133
Yeah.

725
01:00:38,217 --> 01:00:41,303
But how'd you... I mean,
you don't have any superpowers.

726
01:00:41,387 --> 01:00:42,971
- I know.
- Really?

727
01:00:43,055 --> 01:00:46,183
- Yeah.
- Wow. Crazy day for you, huh?

728
01:00:46,267 --> 01:00:49,728
